The article is a transcript of a press briefing given by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs on January 13, 2011. The briefing covers a range of topics, including President Obama's upcoming meeting with President Zardari of Pakistan, the President's speech in Tucson, Arizona following the shooting of Congresswoman Gabrielle Giffords, and the President's views on civility and bipartisanship in politics. Gibbs also responds to questions about gun control, energy policy, and the President's personal response to the tragedy in Tucson.